# Example Configuration for Jenkins OSS Upload
# Copy this file and customize it for your environment

# ========================================
# AWS S3 Example Configuration
# ========================================
# ZIP_FILE_PATH=/path/to/website.zip
# S3_BUCKET=my-website-bucket
# S3_PREFIX=static/v1.0
# CLOUD_PROVIDER=aws
# S3_ENDPOINT=
# S3_REGION=us-east-1
# EMAIL_RECIPIENTS=admin@example.com,dev@example.com
# SMTP_SERVER=smtp.gmail.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@gmail.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-app-password
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=AKIAIOSFODNN7EXAMPLE
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=wJalrXUtnFEMI/K7MDENG/bPxRfiCYEXAMPLEKEY

# ========================================
# Alibaba Cloud OSS Example Configuration
# ========================================
# ZIP_FILE_PATH=/path/to/website.zip
# S3_BUCKET=my-website-bucket
# S3_PREFIX=static/v1.0
# CLOUD_PROVIDER=aliyun
# S3_ENDPOINT=https://oss-cn-hangzhou.aliyuncs.com
# S3_REGION=cn-hangzhou
# EMAIL_RECIPIENTS=admin@example.com
# SMTP_SERVER=smtp.aliyun.com
# SMTP_PORT=465
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@aliyun.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-password
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-access-key-id
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-access-key-secret

# ========================================
# Tencent Cloud COS Example Configuration
# ========================================
# ZIP_FILE_PATH=/path/to/website.zip
# S3_BUCKET=my-website-bucket-1234567890
# S3_PREFIX=static/v1.0
# CLOUD_PROVIDER=tencent
# S3_ENDPOINT=https://cos.ap-guangzhou.myqcloud.com
# S3_REGION=ap-guangzhou
# EMAIL_RECIPIENTS=admin@example.com
# SMTP_SERVER=smtp.qq.com
# SMTP_PORT=587
# SMTP_USERNAME=your-email@qq.com
# SMTP_PASSWORD=your-password
# AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=your-secret-id
# AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=your-secret-key

# ========================================
# Notes:
# ========================================
# 1. For Gmail SMTP, you need to use an "App Password" instead of your regular password
#    Generate one at: https://myaccount.google.com/apppasswords
#
# 2. For Alibaba Cloud, the bucket name format is just "bucket-name"
#    The endpoint should include the region, e.g., oss-cn-hangzhou.aliyuncs.com
#
# 3. For Tencent Cloud, the bucket name format is "bucket-name-appid"
#    The endpoint should include the region, e.g., cos.ap-guangzhou.myqcloud.com
#
# 4. SMTP_PORT common values:
#    - 25: Non-encrypted (not recommended)
#    - 587: TLS/STARTTLS (recommended)
#    - 465: SSL (legacy, but still widely used)
#
# 5. EMAIL_RECIPIENTS can be multiple addresses separated by commas:
#    admin@example.com,dev@example.com,ops@example.com
